
== CONFIG/phon ==

This directory contains the specification files for voice synthesis of pilot
read-back and recognition of ATC instructions in solo sessions.

Every specification line in such file must contain the three fields below in
order, separated by a pipe character ('|', whitespace accepted):
 - the code for the entry (ICAO airline code or navpoint short name);
 - a text-to-speech string allowing virtual pilots to read out the entry;
 - whitespace-separated phonemes expected by the PocketSphinx acoustic model.

Line comments, starting with '#', are allowed.


1. "airline-callsigns.phon"

This file specifies the radio callsigns of airlines, for example "Speedbird" for
British Airways. The airline codes contained are also those used to generate
callsigns when spawning traffic in solo sessions, and to suggest them for
teacher-created traffic.


2. files named "navpoints-XXXX.phon"

Such a file specifies the pronunciation of navpoint names used at location XXXX.
Note that you can always refer to navpoints by spelling out their short code
using the standard aviation alpha-numericals.

